shortdesc.ph: Indicates the error code of calling .

plentry.pd: (1): Token renewal failed due to an unknown server error. It is recommended to check the parameters passed when generating the Token, regenerate the Token, and retry .
(1): Token renewal failed due to an unknown server error. It is recommended to check the parameters passed when generating the Token, regenerate the Token, and retry calling .
(2): Token renewal failed because the passed Token has expired. It is recommended to generate a new Token with a longer expiration time and retry .

(3): Token renewal failed because the Token is invalid. Common causes include:
The App Certificate is enabled in the Agora Console, but the Token is not used when joining the channel. When the App Certificate is enabled, you must use a Token to join the channel.
The specified when calling joinChannel is inconsistent with the used to generate the Token.
The channel name specified when calling joinChannel is inconsistent with the channel name used to generate the Token.

(3): Token renewal failed because the Token is invalid. Common causes include: the App Certificate is enabled in the Agora Console but the Token is not used when joining the channel; the specified when calling the joinChannel method is inconsistent with the used to generate the Token; the channel name specified when calling the joinChannel method is inconsistent with the channel name used to generate the Token.
(4): Token renewal failed because the channel name is invalid. It is recommended to check the channel name, generate a new Token, and retry .
(4): Token renewal failed because the channel name is invalid. It is recommended to check the channel name, generate a new Token, and retry calling .
(5): Token renewal failed because the App ID in the Token is inconsistent with the current App ID. It is recommended to check the App ID, generate a new Token, and retry .
(5): Token renewal failed because the App ID in the Token is inconsistent with the current App ID. It is recommended to check the App ID, generate a new Token, and retry calling .
(6): The previous Token renewal request was canceled due to a new request being initiated.
